      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T11:02:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 652: REMB feedback is now only acted on when the parsed value is exactly 0x6803 or 0x7378, so any real bitrate estimate carried in REMB is ignored. This regresses interoperability with receivers that send an estimated bitrate instead of these legacy sentinel values, causing the sender to miss congestion signals. Treat numeric REMB values as a target/ceiling or preserve the previous handling path for non-sentinel values.\n```suggestion\n        if (br \u003d\u003d 0x6803 || br \u003d\u003d 0x7378) {\n            auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.onRembFeedback(br \u003d\u003d 0x6803);\n            setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n        } else if (br \u003e 0) {\n            setNewBitrate(static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(br / 1000));\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "c56c88e116b588251cc30baeea493dca21f25647",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
