      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T11:02:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 668: The old implementation ignored RR reports with jitter \u003e 1000 on non-Android, but this patch raises the guard to 5000 and applies it on all platforms. That allows multi-second jitter samples to feed the controller, which can produce bogus EWMA state and bitrate decisions from stale/pathological RTCP reports. Keep the existing platform-specific threshold unless there is evidence the larger value is safe.\n```suggestion\n#ifndef __ANDROID__\n        if (rtcpi.jitter \u003e 1000)\n            return;\n#endif\n```",
      "revId": "c56c88e116b588251cc30baeea493dca21f25647",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
