      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T11:02:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 749: The audio congestion path updates the bandwidth controller before calling setupVideoBitrateInfo(), so the controller may still have default limits/target or stale codec limits. That can reduce from 800 Kbps instead of the actual current bitrate, or clamp against 50-4000 even when the negotiated codec range differs. Synchronize limits/current bitrate before feeding the audio-loss signal.\n```suggestion\n        setupVideoBitrateInfo();\n        bwController_.setTargetBitrate(videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent);\n        newBitrate \u003d bwController_.onAudioCongestion(audioPacketLoss);\n```",
